---
import "../../styles/global.css";
import Header from "../../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />

    <meta
      name="viewport"
      content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"
    />

    <title>
      Architecture Complexity Mapping — Go Izumita / 泉田剛
    </title>

    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Research and architectural proposal exploring new urban spatial systems through mapping, RGB analysis, and fragmented architectural representation."
    />

    <meta
      property="og:title"
      content="Architecture Complexity Mapping — Go Izumita / 泉田剛"
    />

    <meta
      property="og:description"
      content="Architecture Research and Graduation Project"
    />

    <meta
      property="og:image"
      content="https://goizumita.com/images/ACMPA-1.JPG"
    />

    <meta
      property="og:type"
      content="website"
    />

    <meta
      property="og:url"
      content="https://goizumita.com/projects/architecture-complexity-mapping"
    />

    <link
      rel="icon"
      href="/favicon.ico"
    />

    <link
      rel="icon"
      type="image/png"
      sizes="48x48"
      href="/favicon.png"
    />
  </head>

  <body>
    <Header />

    <main>
      <h1>
        Architecture Complexity
        Mapping Patterns of
        Architecture
      </h1>

      <p>
        A proposal and research
        project for high-rise
        buildings.
      </p>

      <p>
        By reversing the conventional
        functional hierarchy of
        low-, mid-, and high-rise
        structures, the project
        proposes a more flexible and
        three-dimensional urban
        space.
      </p>

      <p>
        Based on investigations of
        existing buildings, the
        research includes analytical
        methods using RGB additive
        color mixing, as well as a
        research book created by
        layering existing
        architectural drawings onto
        transparent film.
      </p>

      <p>
        It also presents fragmented
        models of individual elements
        without a unified overall
        form, extending the work into
        a proposal for new modes of
        architectural representation
        and presentation.
      </p>

      <p>
        Graduation design project
        from the Department of
        Architecture at Musashino
        Art University.
      </p>

      <p>
        Exhibition Photo:
        Shunsuke Kudo
      </p>

      <img
